/kind bug

For context, I am trying to set up a Minecraft server, which runs on UDP port 19132. I have noticed that when I create a *rootful* container using the flag `-p 19132:19132/udp`, the port forwarding does not seem to work. I confirmed this by running `tcpdump  udp port 19132 -vv` on both the host and the container. The host did receive UDP packets on port 19132, but the container did not.

